SIMPLE: think
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Think
<hw>Think</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Thought</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Thinking</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>thinken</ets>,
properly, to seem, from AS. <ets>⟦thorn⟧yncean</ets> (cf.
<er>Methinks</er>), but confounded with OE. <ets>thenken</ets> to think,
fr. AS. <ets>⟦thorn⟧encean</ets> (imp. <ets>⟦thorn⟧⟦omac⟧hte</ets>);
akin to D. <ets>denken</ets>, <ets>dunken</ets>, OS.
<ets>thenkian</ets>, <ets>thunkian</ets>, G. <ets>denken</ets>,
<ets>d⟦uum⟧nken</ets>, Icel. <ets>⟦thorn⟧ekkja</ets> to perceive, to
know, <ets>⟦thorn⟧ykkja</ets> to seem, Goth. <ets>⟦thorn⟧agkjan</ets>,
<ets>⟦thorn⟧aggkjan</ets>, to think, <ets>⟦thorn⟧ygkjan</ets> to think,
to seem, OL. <ets>tongere</ets> to know. Cf. <er>Thank</er>,
<er>Thought</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To seem or appear; -- used
chiefly in the expressions <xex>methinketh</xex> or <xex>methinks</xex>,
and <xex>methought</xex>.</def> <-- structurally similar to Russ. mne
kazhetsya -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ These are genuine Anglo-Saxon expressions, equivalent to
<xex>it seems to me</xex>, <xex>it seemed to me</xex>. In these
expressions <xex>me</xex> is in the dative case.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To employ any of the intellectual powers except that
of simple perception through the senses; to exercise the higher
intellectual faculties.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>For that I am⟦br⟧
I know, because I <qex>think</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> Specifically: -- <sd>(a)</sd> <def>To call anything to
mind; to remember; <as>as, I would have sent the books, but I did not
<ex>think</ex> of it</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Well <qex>thought</qex> upon; I have it here.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sd>(b)</sd> <def>To reflect upon any subject; to muse; to meditate;
to ponder; to consider; to deliberate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And when he <qex>thought</qex> thereon, he wept.</q> <rj><qau>Mark
xiv. 72.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He <qex>thought</qex> within himself, saying, What shall I do,
because I have no room where to bestow my fruits?</q> <rj><qau>Luke xii.
17.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sd>(c)</sd> <def>To form an opinion by reasoning; to judge; to
conclude; to believe; <as>as, I <ex>think</ex> it will rain
to-morrow</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let them marry to whom they <qex>think</qex> best.</q>
<rj><qau>Num. xxxvi. 6.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sd>(d)</sd> <def>To purpose; to intend; to design; to
mean.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I <qex>thought</qex> to promote thee unto great honor.</q>
<rj><qau>Num. xxiv. 11.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thou <qex>thought'st</qex> to help me.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sd>(e)</sd> <def>To presume; to venture.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Think</qex> not to say within yourselves, We have Abraham to
our father.</q> <rj><qau>Matt. iii. 9.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <xex>To think</xex>, in a philosophical use as yet
somewhat limited, designates the higher intellectual acts, the acts
preeminently rational; to judge; to compare; to reason. Thinking is
employed by Hamilton as ⟦ldquo⟧comprehending all our collective
energies.⟦rdquo⟧ It is defined by Mansel as ⟦ldquo⟧the act of knowing or
judging by means of concepts,⟦rdquo⟧by Lotze as ⟦ldquo⟧the reaction of
the mind on the material supplied by external influences.⟦rdquo⟧ See
<er>Thought</er>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To think better of</b></col>. <cd>See under
<er>Better</er>.</cd> -- <mcol><col><b>To think much of</b></col>,
<it>or</it> <col><b>To think well of</b></col></mcol>, <cd>to hold in
esteem; to esteem highly.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To expect; guess; cogitate; reflect; ponder;
contemplate; meditate; muse; imagine; suppose; believe. See
<er>Expect</er>, <er>Guess</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Think</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Think
<hw>Think</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To conceive; to
imagine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Charity . . . <qex>thinketh</qex> no evil.</q> <rj><qau>1 Cor.
xiii. 4,5.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To plan or design; to plot; to compass.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So little womanhood⟦br⟧
And natural goodness, as to <qex>think</qex> the death⟦br⟧
Of her own son.</q> <rj><qau>Beau. & Fl.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To believe; to consider; to esteem.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Nor <qex>think</qex> superfluous other's aid.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To think much</b></col>, <cd>to esteem a great matter; to
grudge.</cd> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧[He] <xex>thought</xex> not
<xex>much</xex> to clothe his enemies.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Milton.</au> --
<col><b>To think scorn</b></col>. <sd>(a)</sd> <cd>To disdain.</cd>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧He <xex>thought scorn</xex> to lay hands on
Mordecai alone.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Esther iii. 6.</au> <sd>(b)</sd> <cd>To feel
indignation.</cd> <mark>[Obs.]</mark></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Think</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Think
<hw>Think</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Act of thinking; a thought.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧If you think that I'm finished, you've got another <ex>think</ex>
coming!⟦rdquo⟧ <mark>[Obs. or Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thinkable</ent>⟦br⟧
